gist is vendored at `ontology/imports/gistCore.ttl` (resolved offline via
`ontology/catalog-v001.xml`) and is **redistributed** by `make dataset`, which emits it as a
named graph — `https://w3id.org/semanticarts/ontology/gistCore` — inside
`dist/music_dataset.trig`.

CC-BY-4.0 requires attribution on redistribution. This notice, and the `dct:license` /
`dct:source` statements on the ontology header in
`ontology/music_vocabulary_comprehensive.ttl`, are that attribution. Anyone redistributing
`dist/` further must carry it forward.

The Music Vocabulary itself does not modify gist. It reuses gist terms by IRI and never
redefines them, per the project's modelling conventions.
